.DT
add_sign
Disk World creator help
add_sign

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_sign -  This method is used to add a signpost into a specified location in a terrain_map.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void add_sign(int x,
int y,
string sign_long,
mixed sign_read_mess,
string sign_short,
mixed sign_name,
string sign_language)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^title%^RESET%^ - the name of the feature
%^BOLD%^x%^RESET%^ - the x coordinate of the center point
%^BOLD%^y%^RESET%^ - the y coordinate of the center point
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/inherit/terrain_map/handler_base.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method is used to add a signpost into a specified location in a
terrain_map. It is identical to the /std/room/ add_sign, except for
the x and y coordinates which specify where the sign should go.
.EP

.SH Example 1
.SI 5
  add_sign(4, 3, "A wooden signpost.\n",
                 "\n-----------------\n"
                   "| Ladder: East  |\n"
                   "| Bridge: South |\n"
                   "-----------------",
                 "signpost", ({ "signpost", "sign" }), "common");

.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
add_sign

.EP

